hh3cPosa.name: hh3cPosa

revisions.description: Modify the range for hh3cPosaAppID and hh3cPosaBackupAppID in hh3cPosaAppTable. Modify the range for hh3cPosaTerminalTransAppID in hh3cPosaTerminalTable. Modify the range for hh3cPosaMapAppID in hh3cPosaMapTable.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cPosa.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou Technologies. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cPosa.description: This MIB is to provide the definition of the POSA (Point Of Sale Access) system.

Hh3cAppServiceType.name: Hh3cAppServiceType
Hh3cAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server. At present, it supports two service types, tcp(1) and flow(2). If the router connects with the server through SEARIAL/ASYNC interface, the service type is flow(1). If through TCP/IP, the service type is tcp(1).

Hh3cAppMode.name: Hh3cAppMode
Hh3cAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application. It has two value normal(1) and temporary(2). This attribute is valid only when the service type is tcp(1). If it works in temporary(2) mode, the TCP connection between router and application server is established when a POS trade begins and disconnected when a POS trade finishes. In normal(1) mode, the TCP connection is established when POS function is enabled and exists all along.

Hh3cPeerState.name: Hh3cPeerState
Hh3cPeerState.description: The current running state of the peer (application server or POS terminal) of the router. notset(1) The peer is not configured correctly. down(2) The interface connecting with the peer is down. up(3) The interface connecting with the peer is up. kept(4) The connection between router and the peer is not established. linking(5) The connection between router and the peer is establishing. linked(6) The connection between router and the peer is established. multilink(7) There are multiple connections between router and the peer. blocked(8) The connection between router and the peer is unreachable. error(9) Enable failed. The status of down(2) and up(3) appear only when the router and the peer are connected with interface. The status about TCP connections appear when the router and the peer are connected with TCP/IP.

Hh3cTerminalAccessType.name: Hh3cTerminalAccessType
Hh3cTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal. Now it supports 3 types. fcm(1) The POS terminal connects with router through FCM interface. flow(2) The POS terminal connects with router through SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) or AUX interface. tcp(3) The POS terminal connects with router through TCP/IP protocol. The default access type is fcm(2).

Hh3cTpduChangeStrategy.name: Hh3cTpduChangeStrategy
Hh3cTpduChangeStrategy.description: The strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server. Now it supports 2 types. ChangeTpduSrc(1) Replace the source address of the packet with POSID. ChangeTpduDest(2) Replace the destination address of the packet with POSID.

hh3cPosaServerEnable.name: hh3cPosaServerEnable
hh3cPosaServerEnable.description: This attribute controls the starting or stoppage of POS access function. The defalut value is disabled(1).

hh3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.name: hh3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout
hh3cPosaFcmAnswerTimeout.description: The maximum answer time of a POS connection through a FCM (Fast Connection Modem) interface. The answer time is the interval from the POS terminal sending request to the Router giving its reply, in units of milliseconds.

hh3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout.name: hh3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout
hh3cPosaFcmTradeTimeout.description: The maximum time of a POS trade through a FCM interface, in units of milliseconds.

hh3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout.name: hh3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout
hh3cPosaFcmIdleTimeout.description: The maximum idle time of a POS connection through the FCM interface, in units of seconds.

hh3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable
hh3cPosaSrvStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hh3cPosaServerStatusChange trap will be sent or not.

hh3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable
hh3cPosaAppStateChangeTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hh3cPosaAppStateChange trap will be sent or not.

hh3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable
hh3cPosaTerminalHangUpTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hh3cPosaTerminalHangUp trap will be sent or not.

hh3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable
hh3cPosaFcmLnkNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hh3cPosaFcmLinkNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

hh3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable
hh3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailTrapEnable.description: This attribute controls whether the hh3cPosaFcmPhyNegoFailed trap will be sent or not.

hh3cPosaTcpConnectionNumber.name: hh3cPosaTcpConnectionNumber
hh3cPosaTcpConnectionNumber.description: The current number of TCP connections.

hh3cPosaFcmConnectionNumber.name: hh3cPosaFcmConnectionNumber
hh3cPosaFcmConnectionNumber.description: The current number of FCM connections.

hh3cPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable
hh3cPosaTcpConnectionTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the threshold that must be exceeded to send the hh3cPosaTcpConnectionExceed trap.

hh3cPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable
hh3cPosaFcmConnectionTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the threshold that must be exceeded to send the hh3cPosaFcmConnectionExceed trap.

hh3cPosaTcpTradeLimit.name: hh3cPosaTcpTradeLimit
hh3cPosaTcpTradeLimit.description: The limit of concurrent trades in one TCP connection. The value 0 means unlimited.

hh3cPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable.name: hh3cPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable
hh3cPosaTcpTradeTrapEnable.description: This attribute specifies the limit that must be exceeded to send the hh3cPosaTcpTradeExceed trap.

hh3cPosaTcpTradeTimeout.name: hh3cPosaTcpTradeTimeout
hh3cPosaTcpTradeTimeout.description: The maximum interval to wait for the reply from sending the trade packet to the application server. The value 0 means wait forever.

hh3cPosaAppTable.name: hh3cPosaAppTable
hh3cPosaAppTable.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

hh3cPosaAppEntry.name: hh3cPosaAppEntry
hh3cPosaAppEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS application.

hh3cPosaAppID.name: hh3cPosaAppID
hh3cPosaAppID.description: The identification of a POS application.

hh3cPosaAppServiceType.name: hh3cPosaAppServiceType
hh3cPosaAppServiceType.description: The service type of a POS application. It means the way in which the router connects with the application server.

hh3cPosaAppIfIndex.name: hh3cPosaAppIfIndex
hh3cPosaAppIfIndex.description: This attribute is the ifindex through which the router connecting with the application server, if the service type of POS application is flow(2). It is invalid if the service type is tcp(1). At preasent, it supports 5 types of interface: FCM, SERIAL, ASYNC, AM (Analog Modem) and AUX.

hh3cPosaAppMode.name: hh3cPosaAppMode
hh3cPosaAppMode.description: The work mode of a POS application.

hh3cPosaAppHostIPType.name: hh3cPosaAppHostIPType
hh3cPosaAppHostIPType.description: The IP address type of the application server. And now it must be IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppHostIP.name: hh3cPosaAppHostIP
hh3cPosaAppHostIP.description: The IP address of the application server. And now it only supports IPV4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppHostPort.name: hh3cPosaAppHostPort
hh3cPosaAppHostPort.description: The listening port of the application server. If the information of the application server is not specified, this object will return the value 0. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppRouterIPType.name: hh3cPosaAppRouterIPType
hh3cPosaAppRouterIPType.description: The source IP address type of the access router. Now it must be ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppRouterIP.name: hh3cPosaAppRouterIP
hh3cPosaAppRouterIP.description: The source IP address of access router used in connecting with application server. Now it only supports ipv4. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.name: hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval
hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveInterval.description: The TCP keep alive interval of the connection between the router and the application server. In unit of seconds. The default value is 2 seconds. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount.name: hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount
hh3cPosaAppKeepAliveCount.description: The maximum number of sending TCP keep alive packets. It is valid only when the service type is tcp(1).

hh3cPosaAppConnectTimeout.name: hh3cPosaAppConnectTimeout
hh3cPosaAppConnectTimeout.description: The maximum interval that the router waits for the reply from application server after sending the request for establishing a TCP connection. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppState.name: hh3cPosaAppState
hh3cPosaAppState.description: The current running state of application server.

hh3cPosaAppName.name: hh3cPosaAppName
hh3cPosaAppName.description: The description of a POS application.

hh3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable.name: hh3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable
hh3cPosaCallerIDTransEnable.description: Enable or disable the caller-id transmission function.

hh3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy.name: hh3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy
hh3cPosaTpduChangeStrategy.description: Set the strategy to modify the address of the packet from terminals before delivering it to application server.

hh3cPosaBackupAppID.name: hh3cPosaBackupAppID
hh3cPosaBackupAppID.description: Specify the backup application ID, 0 indicates not using backup application. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaQuietTimeOut.name: hh3cPosaQuietTimeOut
hh3cPosaQuietTimeOut.description: Specify the wait time for re-activating application server. It is invalid if the service type is flow(2).

hh3cPosaAppHello.name: hh3cPosaAppHello
hh3cPosaAppHello.description: Specify the switch of hello packet for the application server.

hh3cPosaAppHelloInterval.name: hh3cPosaAppHelloInterval
hh3cPosaAppHelloInterval.description: Specify the interval time in minute(s) of hello packet.

hh3cPosaAppRouterPort.name: hh3cPosaAppRouterPort
hh3cPosaAppRouterPort.description: The source port of access router used in connecting with application server. 0 indicates not to specify the source port. It is valid only if the service type is tcp(1) and mode is normal(1).

hh3cPosaTerminalEntry.name: hh3cPosaTerminalEntry
hh3cPosaTerminalEntry.description: This table shows the configuration information and running status of POS terminal.

hh3cPosaTerminalID.name: hh3cPosaTerminalID
hh3cPosaTerminalID.description: The identification of a POS terminal.

hh3cPosaTerminalAccessType.name: hh3cPosaTerminalAccessType
hh3cPosaTerminalAccessType.description: The access type of a POS terminal.

hh3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.name: hh3cPosaTerminalIfIndex
hh3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface through which connects the POS terminal and the router. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

hh3cPosaTerminalTransAppID.name: hh3cPosaTerminalTransAppID
hh3cPosaTerminalTransAppID.description: The identification of the application server to which all the packets from this POS terminal will be sent. If this object is set to 0, the destination application server to which a packet from this POS terminal will be sent is determined by its TPDU (Transport Protocol Data Unit) destination address. It is invalid if the access type is TCP.

hh3cPosaTerminalListenPort.name: hh3cPosaTerminalListenPort
hh3cPosaTerminalListenPort.description: The listening port accepting the connection from POS terminals. It is valid only when the access type is TCP.

hh3cPosaTerminalState.name: hh3cPosaTerminalState
hh3cPosaTerminalState.description: The current running status of a POS terminal.

hh3cPosaTerminalName.name: hh3cPosaTerminalName
hh3cPosaTerminalName.description: The description of a POS terminal.

hh3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.name: hh3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex
hh3cPosaTerminalCfgIfIndex.description: The ifindex of the interface on which the terminal configuration is. If it is a physical interface, its value is equal to that of hh3cPosaTerminalIfIndex.

hh3cPosaMapTable.name: hh3cPosaMapTable
hh3cPosaMapTable.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

hh3cPosaMapEntry.name: hh3cPosaMapEntry
hh3cPosaMapEntry.description: This table describe the application-mapping information.

hh3cPosaMapDestCode.name: hh3cPosaMapDestCode
hh3cPosaMapDestCode.description: The destination code of the mapping item. Generally, the destination code is a 4-character-string. If the destination address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special destination code, 'default', is for default mapping item.

hh3cPosaMapAppID.name: hh3cPosaMapAppID
hh3cPosaMapAppID.description: The identifier of POS application. It is the index of hh3cPosaAppTable.

hh3cPosaMapSrcCode.name: hh3cPosaMapSrcCode
hh3cPosaMapSrcCode.description: The source code of the mapping item. Generally, the source code is a 4-character-string. If the source address in POS packet matches the code, the packet will be deliveried to the corresponding application server. If any code can not be matched, the packet will be deliveried to the default server. A special source code, 'default', is for default mapping item.
